3.67%    1.696      1 Template:Parentitle\n  3.52%    1.624      1 Template:Chatl\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:324200-0!canonical and timestamp 20220421132620 and revision id 14166940. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{Infobox Task\n|name = Praying to the Gods\n|image = [[File:Chaos Fanatic.png|150px]]\n|task = Kill the Chaos Fanatic 10 times without drinking any potion which restores prayer or leaving the Wilderness.\n|members = Yes\n|release = [[21 July]] [[2021]]\n|update = Combat Achievements\n|area = West of the [[Lava Maze]]\n|reward = None\n|diary = [[Combat Achievements]]\n|tier = [[Combat Achievements/Hard|Hard]]\n}}\n\n'''Praying to the Gods''' is a [[Combat Achievements/Hard|hard combat achievement]] which requires the player to \"Kill the [[Chaos Fanatic]] 10 times without drinking any potion which restores [[prayer]] or leaving the [[Wilderness]].\" Logging out does not reset your progress.\n\nThis task prohibits the consumption of only the following items:\n* [[Prayer potion]]\n* [[Zamorak brew]]\n* [[Super restore]]\n* [[Sanfew serum]]\n\nThis means it is allowed to make use of several other prayer-restoring items, which notably includes the [[Falador shield]]s. [[Jangerberries]] and yellow [[spicy stew]] also do not cause failure of this task, however both of these items are not recommended for practical use. Players can also use the [[special attack]] on the [[Saradomin godsword]] or [[ancient mace]] to recharge their prayer, however due to the fanatic's high melee defences this an unreliable way to restore prayer points.\n\nWhile leaving the [[Wilderness]] is not allowed for this achievement, it is allowed to pray at an [[altar]] and to make use of the [[Wilderness Obelisk]] network. This means the easiest way to achieve this is to gear up for 10 kills of the [[Chaos Fanatic]], and simply pray at an altar to restore prayer points in between the kills. Players with lower [[Prayer]] levels who cannot complete a full kill without recharging their prayer points halfway through the battle can also run away from the fight, pray at an altar, and then continue their kill. Doing so does not reset progress of this achievement.\n\n==Strategy==\n\nThe suggested strategy for completing this task is to make use of the [[Wilderness Obelisk]] network, after having completed the [[Wilderness Diary#Hard|hard Wilderness Diary]] which allows players to set a custom destination. Using these obelisks, players can teleport to the level 13 obelisk, then recharge their prayer at the altar just '''outside''' the [[Ferox Enclave]], and then return to the level 44 obelisk to continue on the task. Note that entering the Enclave does reset progress, so the altar just east of it needs to be used.\n\nPlayers who have not completed the hard Wilderness Diary may opt instead to use the [[Chaos Altar (Prayer)|Chaos Altar]] found in the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|deep Wilderness Chaos Temple]], which is just south-west of the Chaos Fanatic. However, due to this location being commonly patrolled by [[Player killing|PKers]] and being a [[multicombat area]], it is recommended to take more caution when using this altar.\n\n{{Combat Achievements}}"}